<H2>
Our Online Language Materials</H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.native-languages.org/hupa_words.htm
">Hupa Vocabulary</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
List of vocabulary words in the Hupa language, with comparison to words in other Athabaskan languages.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.native-languages.org/hupa_animals.htm
">Hupa Animal Words</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Illustrated glossary of animal words in the Hupa language.
<BR>

<H2>
Hupa Language Lessons and Linguistic Descriptions</H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Linguistic_families_of_Northern_California_Color.jpg
">Linguistic Families of Northern California</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
https://ncidc.org/California_Indian_Pre-Contact_Tribal_Territories
">Pre-Contact California Tribal Territories</A>:</B> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Maps showing where in California the Hupa language is spoken.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.hoopa-nsn.gov/culture/language.htm
">Hoopa Language</a></b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Homepage of the Hoopa Valley Tribe's language department.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.dcn.davis.ca.us/~ammon/danny/Hupa/HupaLanguage.html
">Hupa Language</a></b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Hupa alphabet, numbers and vocabulary.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_hup_phon-1
">Hupa Phonology</a></b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Scanned-in Hupa language materials from the Rosetta Project.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
https://web.archive.org/web/20091027141347/http://www.geocities.com/Athens/9479/wailaki.html
">Athapaskan Placenames of California</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Chart of place names in Hupa, <a href="http://www.native-languages.org/kato.htm">Kato</a>, and <a href="http://www.native-languages.org/wailaki.htm">Wailaki-Sinkyone</a>.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif" alt="*"><b><A HREF="
http://linguistics.berkeley.edu/~survey/languages/hupa.php
">Survey of California Indian Languages: Hupa</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Profile of the Hupa language from the University of California at Berkeley.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://multitree.org/codes/hup.html
">Hupa Language Tree</a>:</b> <br> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Theories about Hupa's language relationships compiled by Linguist List.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://wals.info/languoid/lect/wals_code_hup
">Hupa Language Structures</a>:</b> <br> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Hupa linguistic profile and academic bibliography.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://curtis.library.northwestern.edu/curtis/viewPage.cgi?showp=1&size=2&id=nai.13.book.00000330&volume=13
">West Coast Athapascan Vocabulary</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Early 20th-century wordlists of Hupa, Tolowa and Tututni.
<BR>

<H2>
Hupa Language Preservation and Usage</H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://languagesoftheworld.info/geolinguistics/revitalization-of-the-hupa-language.html
">Revitalization of the Hupa language</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Article on the challenges faced by the Hupa tribe as they work to revive their language.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.ijpr.org/Feature.asp?FeatureID=836
">Rescuing Languages From Extinction </a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Article about Hupa, Yurok, and Karok language revival classes at the Hoopa Valley High School.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www10.gencat.cat/pres_casa_llengues/AppJava/frontend/llengues_detall.jsp?id=1203&idioma=5
">House of Languages: Hupa-Chilula-Whilkut</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Information about Hupa language usage.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=hup
">Ethnologue: Hupa</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Demographic information about the Hupa language.
<BR>

